OL,6,F"It's of such a magnitude that if I
OL,7,Fwas to release it to you now it would
OL,8,Fcertainly be a story."
OL,10,FThe Home Office is now examining the
OL,11,Fnew information closely.
OL,13,FHowever families believe the
OL,14,Fgovernment may hold files that are
OL,15,Fcrucial in examining everything
OL,16,Fsurrounding the bombings - what the
OL,17,Fgovernment and security services knew
OL,18,Fbeforehand and after and what evidence
OL,19,Fthere is which could lead to arrests
OL,20,Fof those responsible.
